Channel: Guild yep - normal guild<br>
players needed: Those that are playing and above 46<br>
Assembly: typically ON call.  Ussually at the raid zone in rides will be arranged if needed.<br>
Time: targets will be assessed from 7 to 8:30 EST Rally times will be after 8 but by 9 PM EST.  I know that this will make some peeps habitually late - sometimes they will be able to come late, other times they won't.  I know we have west coasters that can't even get home from work until 9pm EST - and that is ok - the nature of the beast.<br>
<br>
For those of you that aren't aware there are a number of boss mobs and epic mobs that are contested and rare spawns.  A number of them are on 12 hour, 24 hour, 3 day, 7 day spawn cycles.  During the first day or so after a patch day most guilds chase these rare contested spaws down and snatch them up before we do.   Once they kill the boss mob they &quot;own&quot; the spawn time - meaning they killed it and &quot;know&quot; when it will respawn and are ussually ready to take it down next time it spawns.  While we are not currently arrayed to put this level of time into camping any particular sets of mobs - we are soon going there.  <br>
<br>
For now - Tuesdays will be the one day a week that we dedicate to seeking out and catching a rare/ contested spawn and once catching it up assemble all guildies available/needed to take it down.  Unlike other guilds that have peeps playing as a job  - we have people logging on after work/ dinner / homework / or after wife/husband/G/Bf factioning.  Due to this mob day is only going to be at night during our normal weekday raid schedule.<br>
<br>
Between 7 and 830 our rangers and druids will have certain assignments of zones to Track, look for rare mobs in.  Once a mob meeting our criteria is found he is our guilds focus for the night.  Sometimes we can do a rolling campaign across several zones depending on how plentiful our mobilization crew is.  <br>
<br>
The order of battle for Tuesday Mobilization nights will be the rare contested mobs in our Thread in the private members forum thread(threads).  Once they are gone / not spawned / located - we will take our raiding force and take down any non habitually camped / spawned epic mobs that someone has been waiting on a chance to plow thru.  If neither of the above 2 types of mobs are up/ on our plate - we will have a short list of places to camp to either: <br>
- spawn a spawnable boss<br>
- or simply camp some fair raid level area.<br>
- to a scripted event (Ring of Fire [not yet], PoN maze, tiny knuckles, CT maze, etc)<br>
- Rehearse a raid in a zone that a rare mob spawns.<br>
<br>
An important thing to remember is to keep the time after 8 clear from any exp grind plans.  I would recomend that if you are a non tracker rare mob seeker - this would be a good night to do some solo/guild group work on quests/ factioning / farming/ tradeskilling etc - doing your routine non grind stuff after 7PM so that when the target / assembly / zone is called - you don't have to figure out how to get yourself out of a group etc.  Consider that all that I and most trackers will be doing during this time is running around finding stuff for you to slay and possibly get that phat lewt you have been dreaming of - it is a fair request.<br>
<br>
OK - this post is open for adding to, I will edit some info and move other info to our private forum if it is appropriate.  This thread is dedicated to the mechanics of how we do this.  <br>
<br>
Once we get good at this - there will be times upcomming thru the week when the mobiliztion horn will be sounded and we all use the skills we rehearse on our mobilization day to move and conquer the rare mob that we have been waiting to spawn - before someone else gets to it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub41.ezboard.com/ftribalfury31319frm13.showPrevMessage?topicID=194.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub41.ezboard.com/ftribalfury31319frm13.showNextMessage?topicID=194.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/ftribalfury31319frm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=194.topic><img src=http://www.tribalfury.org/images/addReply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/ftribalfury31319frm13.emailToFriend?topicID=194.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/ftribalfury31319frm13.threadControl?topicID=194.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/ftribalfury31319frm13.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=194.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/subscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to receive email notification of replies"> Click to receive email notification of replies</a> <br>  <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/ftribalfury31319frm13.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=194.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/unsubscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to stop receiving email notification of replies"> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies</a> <br> <